# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# Types:
#   feat:     New feature
#   fix:      Bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation changes
#   style:    Formatting, missing semicolons, etc; no code change
#   refactor: Production code refactoring
#   perf:     Performance improvement
#   test:     Adding missing tests or fixing existing tests
#   build:    Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
#   ci:       Changes to CI files and scripts
#   chore:    Other changes that don't modify src or test files
#   revert:   Reverts a previous commit
#
# Scope (optional): package name (e.g., react, core, styles)
#
# Subject: use imperative, lowercase and don't end with a period
#
# Body (optional): explain what and why, not how
# - Keep lines under 100 characters
# - Use imperative mood
#
# Footer (optional): reference issues, PRs, or breaking changes
# - Closes #123
# - BREAKING CHANGE: description
